"{\"uid\": \"outsideonline.com-outdoor-adventure-olympics-six-paris-olympians\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"(Photo: Andy Astfalck/BSR Agency/Getty)  On July 26, the2024 Olympic Games kick off in Paris, and thousands of athletes will compete for medals across 32 sports over the course of three weeks.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 87, \"end\": 92, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Millions viewers-myself included-will watch some of these Olympic sports and athletes for the first time.\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's part of the fun of the Games: niche sports and lesser-known athletic heroes get a moment in the spotlight.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if you, like me, enjoy these athletes for their impressive backstories and amazing personal histories, I have six individuals for you to follow.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 565, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not even need to know anything about their respective sports to cheer for these stars.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the athletes on this list are medal contenders-others simply have an Olympic backstory that is worthy of our attention.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock is the defending Olympic mountai-bike champion, and he is the favorite to take home gold in Paris.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But his success is not limited to one cycling discipline-Pidcock will represent Great Britain in road cycling as well.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999962042239, \"rank\": 3.330338118350729e-09, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, he's racing in Paris just a few weeks after competing in the Tour de France (he dropped out after stage 9 with COVID symptoms).\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1085, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999993989651544, \"rank\": 5.986987101206325e-07, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a fan of Pidcock because he does absurd and charming biking stunts, likeride 140 mileshome from the airport, or casually pedal from Germany to the Czech Republic the day after winning a cross-country mountain biking World Cup.\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9249760950575489, \"rank\": 0.07959143458689363, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.999859241980844, \"rank\": 0.0001371322451243275, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The man clearly just loves to ride bikes, and I love that about him.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not have to know anything about equestrian to find Mopsie the horse and his rider, five-time Olympian Steffen Peters, wildly entertaining.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9996183527358529, \"rank\": 0.00038179297441803296, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999850457260829, \"rank\": 1.4954497692305317e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renato_Steffen\", \"score\": 0.9893996025530928, \"rank\": 0.010713969770577288, \"text\": \"Steffen\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renato_Steffen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renato_Steffen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the 2020 Olympics in Tokyo, Mopsie and Peters-who is 59 years old-went viral for theirdressage routine.The horse gracefully trotted and hopped in perfect time to a custom-composed EDM beat.\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1628, \"end\": 1633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8213207687582855, \"rank\": 0.21755108097687645, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\", \"score\": 0.9999999770416255, \"rank\": 2.2958316356602758e-08, \"text\": \"EDM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be totally honest, I have never watched a dressage competition in full, but apparently the event isjudgedby how precisely horse and rider execute specific steps and motions, which sounds stuffy and boring until you watch a 900-plus pound animal get down like it's Saturday night at the club (Snoop Dogg himselfhas saidthat Mopsie can \\\"crip-walk\\\" better than most humans).\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 2171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2092, \"end\": 2102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to our friends atClimbing,reigning Olympic gold medalist Janja Garnbret of Slovenia is theathlete to beatin the women's combined boulder and lead climbing event.\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2240, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janja_Garnbret\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Janja Garnbret\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janja_Garnbret\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Janja_Garnbret\"}, {\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7539066598032304, \"rank\": 0.326405224349281, \"text\": \"Slovenia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Japan's Ai Mori is one of a handful of athletes who could challenge Garnbret for the top prize in Paris.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.4436544349559497, \"rank\": 0.6553686906497982, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2357, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ai_Mori\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ai Mori\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ai_Mori\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ai_Mori\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a handful of climbers who could win, includinga few Americans, and the structure of competition may enable Mori to do it in a particularly dramatic fashion.\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\", \"score\": 0.9999999966062205, \"rank\": 3.393738238268793e-09, \"text\": \"Mori\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the combined category, athletes earn scores in two distinct disciplines of the sport, boulder and lead, which are added together for their final ranking.\", \"from\": 2621, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mori holds her own in bouldering in international competitions, but is very good at lead-and since the lead portion of the event is held second, Mori will enter the final rounds with particularly strong chance to improve her overall score.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 3017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\", \"score\": 0.9999999966062205, \"rank\": 3.393738238268793e-09, \"text\": \"Mori\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damian_Mori\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Biles is probably the most recognizable athlete on Team USA, and it almost goes without saying that I am excited to watch her in Paris.\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999105359569569, \"rank\": 8.944224259089121e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3153, \"end\": 3158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not haveany wisdom about her excellance that has not already been shared.\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, I just can not wait to see the seven-time Olympic medalist, 23-time world champion, and best gymnast of all time to get back on the Olympic mat after her case of the \\\"twisties\\\" in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3426, \"end\": 3431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8213207687582855, \"rank\": 0.21755108097687645, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Florence has already cemented his status as one of surfing's all-time greats.\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 32-year-old grew up on the North Shore of Oahu, with legendary waves in his backyard.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3558, \"end\": 3562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oahu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oahu\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oahu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oahu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was winning surf competitions and sponsored by wetsuit and board brand O'Neill when he was just six years old; by the time he turned 23, he waswidely consideredto be the best surfer in the world.\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3676, \"end\": 3683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eugene_O'Neill\", \"score\": 0.9993981757455196, \"rank\": 0.000593135837424629, \"text\": \"O'Neill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eugene_O'Neill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eugene_O'Neill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the years since, he's gone on towin surfing's biggest competitions.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Florence came in ninth in Tokyo and is going into the Paris Olympic competition-which will be held in Tahiti-at the top of the World Surf League rankings.\", \"from\": 3872, \"to\": 4026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3898, \"end\": 3903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8213207687582855, \"rank\": 0.21755108097687645, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3999, \"end\": 4016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.13972780143793e-21, \"text\": \"World Surf League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's hard to put into words exactly what makes Florence such a compelling surfer to watch, especially since I have never surfed in my life, but just watch a minute or two ofthis videoand tell me you are not entertained.\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, Hassan ran in three events (1500 meters, 5000 meters, and 10,000 meters), winning the longest of the three and getting bronze in the 1,500.\", \"from\": 4248, \"to\": 4415, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4276, \"end\": 4282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"score\": 0.899614235663468, \"rank\": 0.11103035048979525, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Hassan, who was born in Ethiopia and competes for the Netherlands, decided to branch out from middle distance to marathons at the 2023 London marathon, she pulled off a stunning come-from-behind victory.\", \"from\": 4416, \"to\": 4624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4421, \"end\": 4427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"score\": 0.899614235663468, \"rank\": 0.11103035048979525, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\"}, {\"begin\": 4445, \"end\": 4453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9704842322731845, \"rank\": 0.03041344173953243, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4475, \"end\": 4486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9952038445462472, \"rank\": 0.004691257837053683, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4556, \"end\": 4571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later that year, in Chicago, she ran the second-fastest women's marathon ever.\", \"from\": 4625, \"to\": 4703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4645, \"end\": 4652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9999373129302953, \"rank\": 5.726397029869901e-05, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hassan has qualified for four events in Paris: 1,500, 5,000, and 10,000 meters, plus the marathon.\", \"from\": 4704, \"to\": 4802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4704, \"end\": 4710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"score\": 0.899614235663468, \"rank\": 0.11103035048979525, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\"}, {\"begin\": 4744, \"end\": 4749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.6870646352279528e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If she decides to compete in all four-which shewon't necessarilyopt to do-she would surpass the already unprecedented competition schedule she pursued in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 4803, \"to\": 4963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4957, \"end\": 4962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8213207687582855, \"rank\": 0.21755108097687645, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And even if Hassan does not participate in every event she's qualified for, her running prowess over such a broad range of distances makes her an athlete worthy of my attention and cheers.\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 5152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4976, \"end\": 4982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"score\": 0.899614235663468, \"rank\": 0.11103035048979525, \"text\": \"Hassan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hasan_ibn_Ali\"}]}]}"